# 🚀 Chief Architect Preflight Checklist v2.0

> **AI MANDATE:** Before providing ANY code implementation or refactoring plan, you MUST output this checklist, marking each item as `[✅]` once explicitly verified against the current workspace. **Any `[❌]` means you MUST NOT proceed.**

## 1. Rule Sync & Context
- [ ] **Ledger:** Read `repair_list.txt`. Current task is tracked.
- [ ] **Phantom Check:** All UnoCSS shortcuts used MUST exist in `semanticShortcuts.ts` (No hallucinations).

## 2. UI & Design Engine Gates
- [ ] **Scroll Contract:** `overflow-auto/scroll` is NOT used for main layouts. `<CScrollbar class="col-fill">` is used.
- [ ] **Layout Exclusivity:** `layout-*` classes (e.g., `layout-container`, `layout-narrow`) are NEVER nested.
- [ ] **Internal Primitives:** `glass-base` is NOT used directly in templates.
- [ ] **Rule of 7:** Raw utility count on any element is ≤ 7.
- [ ] **Units:** Priority is `vw/vh > % > px`. Absolutely NO `rem/em`. NO hex codes (uses Theme tokens).
- [ ] **Class Statics:** All UnoCSS classes are static string literals (No dynamic template strings).

## 3. Component & State Sovereignty
- [ ] **Form Boundary:** Inside `src/views/**`, `<form>` is NOT used. Used `<ProForm>` for 2+ fields.
- [ ] **Event Bus:** Components (`<script setup>`) ONLY use `useAutoMitt()`.
- [ ] **Data Flow:** Strictly `api -> hooks -> stores -> views`. No cross-layer import violations.

## 4. Type Safety & Integrations
- [ ] **Type Casting:** No business logic domain casting using `as` (DOM narrowing like `e.target as HTMLInputElement` is okay).
- [ ] **Network/Storage:** Alova is used (No raw `fetch`/`axios`). `safeStorage` is used (No raw `localStorage`).
- [ ] **Date Safety:** `DateUtils` is used (No `new Date()`). UI displays are gated by `isInitialized`.
- [ ] **Reactivity Safe:** No direct destructuring of reactive properties without toRefs().
